<subSubSection id="88916555ED5E7D7ABC54F637C2A07ACE" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C03436DEED5E7D7ABC54F637C2A07ACE" blockId="3.[2067,2661,2463,2886]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="078B4D5DED5E7D7ABC54F637C3837A3D" authorityName="Vinogradov" authorityYear="1922" box="[2069,2218,2538,2571]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Salpingotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Salpingotus</taxonomicName>
thomas: is in the subgenus Prosalpingotus. According to Vinogradov in 1928 and based on the published description of W. Griffith’s Afghanistan route, most probable type locality was somewhere between Afghan—Pakistan border and Kandahar. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88916555ED5E7D7ABC55F4DFC2E77B70" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="multiple">
<caption id="94F46656ED5E7D7ABC55F4DFC2E77B70" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6591956" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6591956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6591956/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" startId="3.[2068,2240,2818,2847]" targetBox="[1453,2044,2471,2884]" targetPageId="3">
